The paper deals with the practical aspects of the MAXCUT problem, which is a well-known problem in computer science and optimization. The techniques used in the paper involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), combinatorics and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). These sub-categories are all relevant to the problem and the methods used in the paper.
